# Rocket.new — Web Tech Stack Expert Reference

## What Rocket Generates for Web Apps
- **React** → JavaScript, Tailwind CSS
- **Next.js** → TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, App Router
- **Backend**: Supabase (PostgreSQL, Auth, Storage, Edge Functions)
- **Deployment**: Netlify (auto, one-click)

Rocket uses the **Next.js App Router** (not Pages Router). All pages live in the `/app` directory.

---

## Project File Structure (Next.js — Most Common)
```
/
├── app/
│   ├── page.tsx              # Home page (/)
│   ├── layout.tsx            # Root layout wrapping all pages
│   ├── globals.css           # Global styles
│   └── [route]/
│       └── page.tsx          # Dynamic route pages
├── components/               # Reusable React components
│   ├── ui/                   # Base UI elements (buttons, inputs, cards)
│   └── [feature]/            # Feature-specific components
├── lib/
│   └── supabase.ts           # Supabase client (browser + server)
├── public/                   # Static assets (images, fonts, icons)
├── .env.local                # Local environment variables (never committed)
├── next.config.js            # Next.js configuration
├── tailwind.config.ts        # Tailwind configuration
└── package.json              # Dependencies
```

## Project File Structure (React — Simpler Apps)
```
/
├── src/
│   ├── App.jsx               # Root component + routes
│   ├── main.jsx              # Entry point
│   ├── pages/                # Page components
│   ├── components/           # Reusable components
│   └── lib/
│       └── supabase.js       # Supabase client
├── public/
├── .env.local
├── vite.config.js            # Vite build config
└── package.json
```

