## GitHub Integration

### Setup (One-Way Export)
1. Project Settings → Integrations → GitHub → authorize
2. Choose: create new repo OR push to existing
3. Click Push — Rocket pushes all code to GitHub

### After GitHub Export
```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/your-repo
cd your-repo
npm install
cp .env.example .env.local   # add your Supabase keys
npm run dev                  # runs on localhost:3000
```

### Limitations
- **One-way only**: Rocket → GitHub. Cannot import GitHub code back into Rocket.
- **No auto-sync**: After export, changes in Rocket must be manually pushed to GitHub again
- **Two-way sync**: On the roadmap, not yet available

